# Excludes for the `fargate/rpa_runner/Dockerfile` build context.
#
# CDK uses the repo root as the build context (see
# infra/components/rpa.py:RpaRunnerImage) so the Dockerfile can `COPY`
# from both `fargate/rpa_runner/` and `lambda/multi-org/`. Everything
# else is wasted bytes — and a few things (cdk.out, .git, node_modules)
# cause real problems if included.

# CDK synthesizes assets into cdk.out under each asset's own subdir,
# which without this exclude recurses infinitely when the build context
# is the repo root that contains cdk.out.
infra/cdk.out
**/cdk.out

# Version-control + IDE noise
.git
.github
.vscode
.idea

# Node / Python / OS noise
node_modules
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
.DS_Store
htmlcov
.coverage*

# Tests + docs aren't needed in the runner image; the runner imports
# from `lambda/multi-org/rpa/` and `lambda/multi-org/audit/` only.
lambda/tests
docs

# Frontend assets — not needed in the Python runner.
admin-ui/node_modules
admin-ui/dist

# Local env files must never enter the image.
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*
